============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is an algorithm?
A1: An algorithm is a step-by-step procedure for solving a
     problem. Algorithms have inputs, defined steps, and
     outputs. Examples: sorting, searching, path-finding.

Q2: What is the internet?
A2: The internet is a global network of interconnected
     computers using TCP/IP protocols. It began as ARPANET
     in 1969 and became public with the World Wide Web in
     1994.

Q3: What is relativity?
A3: Einstein's relativity: Special (1905) — time dilates,
     mass increases at high speeds; E=mc². General (1915) —
     gravity is curved spacetime; explains black holes and
     expanding universe.

Q4: What is the water cycle?
A4: Water evaporates from oceans/lakes, rises and condenses
     into clouds, falls as precipitation, and flows back via
     rivers and groundwater. Driven by solar energy.

Q5: What is the Big Bang?
A5: The Big Bang theory states the universe began from an
     extremely hot, dense point approximately 13.8 billion
     years ago and has been expanding ever since.

